cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IR 

This paper is likely to belong to the arXiv CS sub-category cs.CL (Computation and Language) as it deals with natural language processing tasks such as machine transliteration. The paper also proposes a character-based encoder-decoder model that uses recurrent neural networks, which falls under the sub-categories of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The use of attention mechanisms in the proposed model also suggests a possible fit under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the experiments conducted in the paper involve the evaluation of different datasets, which could potentially place it under cs.IR (Information Retrieval).
